# Parenting Systems

A curated list of approaches, tools, and resources that help translate parenting theory into daily practice.

---

## Foundations

- [Raising Children Network](https://raisingchildren.net.au/) – Evidence-based parenting guidance translated into practical, everyday actions.
- [Zero to Three](https://www.zerotothree.org/) – Research-backed resources focused on early childhood development.
- [The Whole-Brain Child](https://www.drdansiegel.com/books/the-whole-brain-child/) – Framework for understanding and responding to children’s behavior through brain development.

---

## Sleep & Routines

- [Huckleberry](https://huckleberrycare.com/) – Wake window tracking and sleep guidance for infants and toddlers.
- [Taking Cara Babies](https://takingcarababies.com/) – Structured routines combining multiple sleep approaches into practical guidance.
- [Possums Sleep](https://possumsonline.com/) – Sleep approach based on biological rhythms and reducing parent stress.

---

## Feeding & Meals

- [Solid Starts](https://solidstarts.com/) – Database and guides for introducing solids safely and confidently.
- [Kids Eat in Color](https://kidseatincolor.com/) – Practical strategies for picky eating and balanced nutrition.
- [Feeding Littles](https://feedinglittles.com/) – Responsive feeding and mealtime structure.

---

## Emotion & Behavior

- [Big Little Feelings](https://biglittlefeelings.com/) – Toddler behavior strategies grounded in emotional validation and boundaries.
- [How to Talk So Little Kids Will Listen](https://www.how-to-talk.com/) – Communication tools that reduce conflict and increase cooperation.

---

## Play & Development

- [Lovevery Blog](https://lovevery.com/community/blog) – Developmentally appropriate play ideas and explanations.
- [Khan Academy Kids](https://learn.khanacademy.org/khan-academy-kids/) – Free early learning content and activities.

---

## Parent Wellbeing

- [The Nap Ministry](https://thenapministry.com/) – Reframing rest as essential, not optional.
- [Headspace](https://www.headspace.com/) – Meditation and mental health support for busy parents.

---

## Couple Connection After Kids

- [The Gottman Institute](https://www.gottman.com/) – Research-based relationship tools and communication frameworks.
- [Fair Play](https://www.fairplaylife.com/) – System for dividing household and family responsibilities.

---

## Bilingual & Cultural Life

- [OPOL (One Parent One Language)](https://bilingualfamily.eu/one-parent-one-language-opol/) – Structured approach to raising bilingual children.
- [Multilingual Parenting](https://multilingualparenting.com/) – Practical guidance for raising children with multiple languages.

---

## Household Systems Supporting Parenting

- [Cozi](https://www.cozi.com/) – Family calendar and organization app.
- [Notion](https://www.notion.so/) – Flexible tool for building custom family systems and trackers.

---

## Notes

This list prioritizes:
- clarity over volume  
- practical application over theory  
- sustainability over intensity  

It is intentionally limited and curated.
